WEBVTT

00:03.699 --> 00:04.047
.

00:04.091 --> 00:06.093
- Previously
on "The Endgame"...

00:06.136 --> 00:08.008
- Bank just got hit
by six gunmen.

00:08.051 --> 00:09.052
[explosion]

00:09.096 --> 00:10.314
- She thinks on a big scale.

00:10.358 --> 00:11.837
And the biggest bank
in New York is--

00:11.881 --> 00:13.056
- Federal Reserve.

00:13.100 --> 00:14.971
- How's she gonna
steal 6,000 tons of gold?

00:15.015 --> 00:16.320
[gunfire]

00:16.364 --> 00:18.018
- What's happening?

00:18.061 --> 00:20.063
- The woman they took
is Ameera Ojjeh.

00:20.107 --> 00:22.631
She has the biometrics
to open the vault.

00:22.674 --> 00:26.722
- I took over seven banks
but not for money.

00:26.765 --> 00:28.071
[explosion]

00:28.115 --> 00:29.768
We have to be alive
to get our revenge.

00:29.812 --> 00:32.423
So when's the last time
you thought of Isaac Bigby?

00:32.467 --> 00:33.903
- Who the hell is Isaac Bigby?

00:33.946 --> 00:35.426
- The man who killed
my mother.

00:35.470 --> 00:38.081
- You actually turned
your husband in to the FBI.

00:38.125 --> 00:40.344
- You, Sergey--
there's more to this.

00:40.388 --> 00:42.825
- Just walk away,
and don't come back.

00:42.868 --> 00:44.044
- Who are the Beloks?

00:44.087 --> 00:45.654
- Complicated question.

00:45.697 --> 00:47.699
- The Ukrainian
organized crime family.

00:47.743 --> 00:50.180
Every story from her has
yielded sideways information

00:50.224 --> 00:51.964
about her next target.

00:52.008 --> 00:54.924
- Val has access and insight
the rest of us don't.

00:54.967 --> 00:56.534
I listen to her.
You should too.

00:56.578 --> 00:57.840
- That sounds like a demotion.

00:57.883 --> 00:59.102
- It's reality, Doak.

00:59.146 --> 01:01.365
- How is she receiving
the information?

01:01.409 --> 01:03.672
- Texts, all ones and zeros.

01:03.715 --> 01:05.282
- All of your targets
are in this photo.

01:05.326 --> 01:07.284
The others, are they next?

01:07.328 --> 01:09.243
- Val Turner will discover it.

01:10.331 --> 01:13.464
[water running]

01:20.167 --> 01:22.517
both: Mm.

01:22.560 --> 01:24.910
- You're so domestic.
- [laughs]

01:24.954 --> 01:26.564
- I love it.

01:26.608 --> 01:30.090
- Don't get used to it.
It's a special occasion.

01:30.133 --> 01:33.049
[tense music]

01:33.093 --> 01:34.268
♪

01:34.311 --> 01:36.313
- Let's finish this.

01:36.357 --> 01:43.494
♪

01:45.192 --> 01:48.325
- Please, I've told you
everything.

01:48.369 --> 01:51.415
- You told us a bit, Pasha,

01:51.459 --> 01:54.201
although
it took some convincing.

01:54.244 --> 01:57.769
But you have not told us
everything, not yet.

01:57.813 --> 01:59.423
- You're afraid.

01:59.467 --> 02:02.122
We are talking
about powerful people.

02:02.165 --> 02:04.776
But right now, we are the ones
you should be afraid of.

02:04.820 --> 02:08.780
- I admit, I planted the bomb
in the church.

02:08.824 --> 02:15.787
♪

02:17.876 --> 02:20.357
My wife was sick.

02:20.401 --> 02:22.620
I couldn't afford a doctor.

02:22.664 --> 02:25.449
They offered me so much money.

02:25.493 --> 02:28.365
- Your wife is better now?
She's good?

02:28.409 --> 02:31.847
- It was too late.
It was all for nothing.

02:31.890 --> 02:33.370
I'm so sorry.

02:33.414 --> 02:37.331
- The person who hired you,
give us a name.

02:38.288 --> 02:40.290
- If I do, you'll just kill me.

02:40.334 --> 02:44.164
- No, I will not kill you.

02:45.774 --> 02:48.168
I promise.

02:49.169 --> 02:50.561
It's all right.

02:52.389 --> 02:54.522
Whisper it to me.

02:57.089 --> 02:59.135
- [whispering indistinctly]

02:59.179 --> 03:01.833
- [sighs]

03:01.877 --> 03:04.358
You took so much
from us, Pasha.

03:08.710 --> 03:11.365
Murdered my husband's
entire family,

03:11.408 --> 03:12.714
destroyed our lives.

03:12.757 --> 03:17.327
We have lived with this grief
for so long.

03:18.633 --> 03:22.724
I see you have remorse,
but is that justice?

03:23.986 --> 03:26.902
And yet I made a promise.

03:26.945 --> 03:30.253
So I will not kill you.

03:30.297 --> 03:33.038
- [whimpers]
- He will.

03:33.082 --> 03:36.825
- [grunting]

03:36.868 --> 03:38.392
[neck cracks]

03:38.435 --> 03:40.437
- A small justice
was done that day

03:40.481 --> 03:42.265
but nowhere near enough.

03:42.309 --> 03:47.009
- So Pasha Antonov admitted
that he was hired by a member

03:47.052 --> 03:50.578
of the Cutler administration
to bomb your wedding?

03:51.448 --> 03:53.276
Someone in this photo?

03:53.320 --> 03:55.060
Care to share
and save me the trouble

03:55.104 --> 03:56.975
of finding out myself?

03:58.542 --> 04:01.197
Why would a U.S. official

04:01.241 --> 04:03.895
put a hit
on the Vodianov family?

04:03.939 --> 04:07.247
- When you meet that person,
perhaps you can ask them.

04:07.290 --> 04:09.727
- I ran the dates of when
these people worked for Cutler

04:09.771 --> 04:12.513
and checked the White House
sign-in logs.

04:12.556 --> 04:14.819
They're watching drone footage
of the church explosion,

04:14.863 --> 04:15.777
aren't they?

04:18.345 --> 04:20.782
- They're watching the massacre

04:20.825 --> 04:24.960
of 108 men, women,
and children.

04:26.353 --> 04:28.398
- A nightmare.

04:28.442 --> 04:30.270
- To say the least.

04:32.315 --> 04:34.622
- Haven't you already
made your point?

04:34.665 --> 04:36.798
The city's been at a standstill
for a week,

04:36.841 --> 04:39.279
and innocent people
are still being held hostage.

04:39.322 --> 04:41.585
Four of the officials
in this photo

04:41.629 --> 04:43.718
are currently facing charges.

04:43.761 --> 04:45.589
- I see others in this photo

04:45.633 --> 04:47.591
who currently face
nothing at all.

04:47.635 --> 04:49.419
- Okay,
so I'll make you a deal.

04:49.463 --> 04:51.465
In exchange for the banks
you hold,

04:51.508 --> 04:53.728
we'll investigate the others.

04:53.771 --> 04:57.253
- You're already doing this,
except I have leverage.

04:57.297 --> 05:00.212
But I like the idea
of teamwork.

05:00.256 --> 05:01.692
- I wouldn't say we're a team.

05:01.736 --> 05:04.782
- [laughs]
Now, now, you never know

05:04.826 --> 05:07.089
when someone might turn out
to be a true partner.

05:07.132 --> 05:10.440
I won't stop until there is
full accountability.

05:10.484 --> 05:13.617
It's your mother's birthday
this week, no?

05:14.879 --> 05:17.621
She would still be here
with you

05:17.665 --> 05:22.278
if one man hadn't chosen
the path of violence.

05:22.322 --> 05:24.454
Don't you wish you could hold
the Isaac Bigby accountable

05:24.498 --> 05:26.413
for everything
he took from you?

05:26.456 --> 05:28.110
- Bigby is dead.

05:30.417 --> 05:32.244
I've accepted the fact

05:32.288 --> 05:35.639
that there won't be
any justice for my mother.

05:35.683 --> 05:38.120
- But what if there could be?

05:39.339 --> 05:42.124
What if you could talk to him?

05:42.167 --> 05:43.778
Would you show him more mercy

05:43.821 --> 05:46.781
than Sergey and I
showed Pasha Antonov?

05:46.824 --> 05:48.957
- I don't deal
in hypotheticals.

05:49.000 --> 05:52.047
I deal in reality,
the here and now.

05:52.090 --> 05:54.789
- Hmm. You dwell
in the past too, don't lie.

05:57.357 --> 05:58.532
- Who's next?

05:58.575 --> 06:00.795
- You'll see.

06:02.449 --> 06:05.539
[siren wailing]

06:07.018 --> 06:09.064
[dramatic music]

06:09.107 --> 06:11.675
- We need to get to door three
in time for the iris scan.

06:11.719 --> 06:13.938
Sebastian, Garcelle,
grab the boy.

06:13.982 --> 06:16.506
Liam...

06:16.550 --> 06:17.899
bring the briefcase
and wire it up.

06:17.942 --> 06:18.769
Let's go.

06:18.813 --> 06:21.946
[suspenseful music]

06:21.990 --> 06:24.514
♪

06:24.558 --> 06:26.516
- Where are you taking us?

06:26.560 --> 06:27.865
- Okay, I'm coming.

06:27.909 --> 06:29.650
- We're all going down
to the vault.

06:29.693 --> 06:32.435
You will do exactly as I say.

06:32.479 --> 06:39.573
♪

06:44.491 --> 06:47.450
[gas hissing]

06:53.935 --> 06:56.067
- I need to update
the president.

06:56.111 --> 06:57.895
So they breached
the stairwell gate or...

06:57.939 --> 06:59.984
- They're in the process
and likely to soon.

07:00.028 --> 07:02.291
But that doesn't mean they're
in the gold vault yet, ma'am.

07:02.334 --> 07:03.640
- So you called
the White House chief of staff

07:03.684 --> 07:05.294
to say all is right
with the world?

07:05.337 --> 07:06.730
Get to it.

07:06.774 --> 07:08.428
- That stairwell does lead
to the subterranean levels

07:08.471 --> 07:09.559
and the gold.

07:09.603 --> 07:11.996
- But past extensive
security layers.

07:12.040 --> 07:13.258
- Rogelio,
your assistant director

07:13.302 --> 07:14.695
needs to stop sugarcoating.

07:14.738 --> 07:16.871
We are neck-deep
in fresh sewage.

07:16.914 --> 07:19.961
If the 6,000 tons of gold
in that vault is removed,

07:20.004 --> 07:23.617
tampered with, touched,
posed with for a selfie,

07:23.660 --> 07:25.270
the world will say
the United States

07:25.314 --> 07:27.925
cannot protect its assets,
and the dollar will plummet.

07:27.969 --> 07:30.580
We're talking
global depression.

07:30.624 --> 07:32.234
- Look, we will do
everything in our power

07:32.277 --> 07:33.714
to keep that from happening.

07:33.757 --> 07:35.193
- The president's
in the press room at 3:00 p.m.

07:35.237 --> 07:36.630
Is that what he should
tell those vipers?

07:36.673 --> 07:39.459
- Ma'am, there are two other
recognizable people

07:39.502 --> 07:40.634
in that photo.

07:40.677 --> 07:42.331
One of them
will be her next target.

07:42.374 --> 07:43.593
We're working on that now.

07:43.637 --> 07:44.942
- I know Judge Caroline Walsh.

07:44.986 --> 07:46.161
Don't know why
she'd be a target.

07:46.204 --> 07:47.510
- Same.

07:47.554 --> 07:48.859
Still, I'm putting a detail
on her home.

07:48.903 --> 07:51.122
- The other is Ahmed Abdel.

07:51.166 --> 07:54.169
In 2011, he was an assistant
in the Cutler staff.

07:54.212 --> 07:55.562
- We're digging into companies
he's founded

07:55.605 --> 07:57.085
after leaving the White House?

07:57.128 --> 08:01.306
Opal Electronics,
Sable Gaming, TITN Consultants.

08:01.350 --> 08:02.830
- TITN?

08:02.873 --> 08:05.485
Four years ago, they did
a complete security revamp

08:05.528 --> 08:07.051
at the Federal Reserve.

08:07.095 --> 08:08.662
- So if anyone
can stop Snow White

08:08.705 --> 08:11.447
from stealing the gold,
it's him.

08:11.491 --> 08:15.059
- Which would put Abdel number
one on Fedorova's hit list.

08:15.103 --> 08:17.018
Bring him in.
- I'm on my way.

08:19.237 --> 08:20.500
- What's her name again?

08:20.543 --> 08:21.936
- Val Turner.

08:21.979 --> 08:23.590
- And, Flowers,
you're her partner?

08:23.633 --> 08:24.982
- That's right, ma'am.

08:25.026 --> 08:26.810
- Keep doing
what you're doing.

08:26.854 --> 08:28.508
I'll brief the president now.

08:31.467 --> 08:33.382
- Yeah.

08:34.035 --> 08:36.254
Just keep doing
what you're doing.

08:39.214 --> 08:40.607
[exhales heavily]

08:40.650 --> 08:47.788
♪

08:51.966 --> 08:53.184
- You got
through the first gate,

08:53.228 --> 08:54.403
but you're gonna need
a lot more than that

08:54.446 --> 08:55.622
to get to the gold.

09:01.802 --> 09:04.195
- Something like this?
[device beeps]

09:04.239 --> 09:05.414
- No!

09:05.457 --> 09:07.677
- Wired up, ready to go.

09:10.071 --> 09:11.768
- What are you planning
to do with that?

09:11.812 --> 09:14.249
- Sir, I'm a mother
with two little girls at home.

09:14.292 --> 09:15.946
I am begging you,
please don't hurt me.

09:15.990 --> 09:18.035
- Don't give me a reason to.

09:18.079 --> 09:24.215
♪

09:28.916 --> 09:31.005
- We've tracked
the coded messages

09:31.048 --> 09:33.616
being sent to Fedorova
via the War Room console.

09:33.660 --> 09:35.357
Most originated
from cell phones

09:35.400 --> 09:36.750
inside the hijacked banks.

09:36.793 --> 09:39.796
- Snow White members
keeping Fedorova up to speed.

09:39.840 --> 09:41.363
- But there's an outlier.

09:41.406 --> 09:42.930
A third of those messages

09:42.973 --> 09:45.933
were sent from a cell phone
north of the city.

09:49.197 --> 09:50.981
- Peekskill
Correctional Facility.

09:51.025 --> 09:53.723
- Mm, the only person I can
think of inside of that prison

09:53.767 --> 09:56.639
sending messages
is Owen Turner.

09:57.466 --> 09:58.772
- Yeah.

10:04.647 --> 10:06.649
[doorbell rings]

10:06.693 --> 10:08.085
- Mr. Abdel?

10:08.129 --> 10:09.130
- Yes?

10:09.173 --> 10:12.829
- Special Agent Val Turner,
FBI.

10:12.873 --> 10:14.091
Sorry to drop in unannounced,

10:14.135 --> 10:16.354
but you don't
pick up your phone.

10:16.398 --> 10:17.617
Do you have a minute?

10:17.660 --> 10:19.270
- I don't, no.

10:19.314 --> 10:22.143
- Yeah, that was just me
being polite.

10:22.186 --> 10:24.754
I'm here on the authority
of the director of the FBI

10:24.798 --> 10:25.842
and the White House.

10:25.886 --> 10:27.278
Open the door.

10:31.500 --> 10:33.154
- What do you want?

10:33.197 --> 10:35.286
- Look, Snow White operatives
are trying to breach

10:35.330 --> 10:38.028
the Federal Reserve's
gold vault.

10:38.072 --> 10:41.902
I have it on good authority
that you can help us stop them.

10:41.945 --> 10:44.078
- I do not know
what you're talking about.

10:44.121 --> 10:45.470
- Mr. Abdel,

10:45.514 --> 10:47.690
unless you want to end up
indicted, humiliated,

10:47.734 --> 10:50.780
or whatever else
Fedorova has planned for you,

10:50.824 --> 10:53.783
help me, and I'll help you.

10:54.697 --> 10:55.655
- [scoffs]

10:55.698 --> 10:57.178
[lock clicks]

10:58.614 --> 11:00.050
It runs off the phone.

11:00.094 --> 11:01.748
- What doesn't these days?

11:04.011 --> 11:06.143
- I heard her name on the news,
that's it.

11:06.187 --> 11:07.884
I don't understand
why I'd be a target.

11:07.928 --> 11:10.278
- Well, most of the other
people in this photo were.

11:10.321 --> 11:13.194
So it stands to reason
you're next.

11:13.237 --> 11:15.979
- Oh, God.
Where did that come from?

11:16.023 --> 11:18.155
- Where do you think?

11:18.199 --> 11:19.853
- Okay, uh,

11:19.896 --> 11:22.116
I was just operating
the drone camera.

11:22.159 --> 11:24.118
I was technical assistance.

11:24.161 --> 11:25.685
They pulled me in
at the last minute,

11:25.728 --> 11:26.729
but I didn't know
what it was about,

11:26.773 --> 11:27.817
not until it was over.

11:27.861 --> 11:28.992
I didn't do anything to her.

11:29.036 --> 11:30.777
- I'm not sure
she sees it that way.

11:30.820 --> 11:32.126
- Okay, does she know
that Joan Bradbury

11:32.169 --> 11:33.301
said that if I told anyone,

11:33.344 --> 11:35.651
she would revoke
my citizenship,

11:35.695 --> 11:37.522
deport my parents
back to Syria?

11:37.566 --> 11:38.698
I'm innocent here.

11:40.308 --> 11:42.789
- You've been waiting for me,
haven't you?

11:44.051 --> 11:46.662
- Or her.
I've seen what's been going on.

11:46.706 --> 11:49.839
It's been like a--like a vise
tightening around my throat.

11:49.883 --> 11:51.623
- You want it to stop?

11:51.667 --> 11:54.061
Help us keep Snow White out
of the Reserve's gold vault.

11:54.104 --> 11:56.324
- You are assuming
there's a way in.

11:56.367 --> 11:58.108
- If you built it,
you can crack it.

12:00.241 --> 12:02.112
- Okay.
There is a trapdoor.

12:02.156 --> 12:04.158
So if the system
was ever compromised,

12:04.201 --> 12:05.681
I could log in
and manually reset it.

12:05.725 --> 12:09.206
The only thing is, I need to be
on the Reserve's server.

12:09.250 --> 12:11.731
- Great. Let's talk on the way.
[cell phone chimes]

12:11.774 --> 12:13.341
- What the hell is this?

12:13.384 --> 12:16.910
I don't suppose you brought
any other agents with you.

12:16.953 --> 12:18.999
- No, they're
definitely not with me.

12:19.042 --> 12:21.784
Um, where can you take cover?

12:21.828 --> 12:23.177
- Fr-fr-fr-from whom?

12:23.220 --> 12:24.656
- Ahmed.

12:24.700 --> 12:26.615
- There is--there is
a safe room off the library.

12:26.658 --> 12:27.790
- Good, go.

12:27.834 --> 12:29.487
Wait, your phone,
it controls the house?

12:29.531 --> 12:30.793
Unlock it, give it to me.

12:31.838 --> 12:34.405
Okay, go.

12:34.449 --> 12:37.408
[tense music]

12:37.452 --> 12:41.891
♪

12:41.935 --> 12:43.850
- Val, do you have Abdel?

12:43.893 --> 12:45.242
- Three armed gunmen

12:45.286 --> 12:47.244
just showed up
wearing Snow White masks.

12:47.288 --> 12:48.985
I think she's trying
to take him out.

12:49.029 --> 12:50.595
- I'll send backup.
Hold them off.

12:50.639 --> 12:57.559
♪

13:25.195 --> 13:26.936
- FBI!
Drop your weapon!

13:26.980 --> 13:28.982
[gunshots]

13:36.076 --> 13:38.730
[rapid gunfire]

13:38.774 --> 13:40.123
[gunshots]

13:47.739 --> 13:47.914
.

13:47.957 --> 13:49.654
[rapid gunfire]

13:51.047 --> 13:52.701
[gunshot, gun clicks]

13:53.745 --> 13:54.834
- Damn it!

13:57.184 --> 13:59.751
- Come on out now.

13:59.795 --> 14:01.144
Game's over.

14:01.797 --> 14:03.930
[TV blaring,
pinball machines blipping]

14:03.973 --> 14:05.975
[toy car whirring]

14:07.890 --> 14:09.152
[rapid gunfire]

14:09.196 --> 14:12.112
[pop music blaring]

14:12.155 --> 14:13.504
♪

14:13.548 --> 14:15.855
- [breathing heavily]

14:16.725 --> 14:17.639
- You're supposed to be
in the safe room.

14:17.682 --> 14:18.770
There's another gunman.

14:18.814 --> 14:20.642
- The safe room door,
it's stuck.

14:20.685 --> 14:22.209
- How can it be stuck?

14:22.252 --> 14:23.384
- Because it's needed.

14:23.427 --> 14:25.560
That's when technology
always fails.

14:25.603 --> 14:27.431
Give me my phone.

14:33.873 --> 14:36.136
[glass shatters]

14:36.179 --> 14:37.572
- That's the third shooter.

14:39.574 --> 14:41.924
- Call it off.

14:41.968 --> 14:43.317
Right now!

14:43.360 --> 14:45.188
- I don't understand.

14:45.232 --> 14:46.973
- Tell your men to stand down.

14:47.016 --> 14:49.105
Any harm comes to Turner,
the same comes to you.

14:50.454 --> 14:53.936
- Harm Agent Turner?
Why would I do this?

14:59.028 --> 15:01.509
- You better pray the state
police get to them in time.

15:01.552 --> 15:08.603
♪

15:26.229 --> 15:28.362
- I know you're in there.

15:28.405 --> 15:31.452
Come on out real easy, man.

15:31.495 --> 15:33.758
Don't make me come in there
and get you.

15:33.802 --> 15:35.108
Ah!

15:35.151 --> 15:37.545
[glass shatters]

15:40.330 --> 15:42.202
- Get out here.
- Are we good?

15:42.245 --> 15:43.943
- Great.

15:45.292 --> 15:46.510
- Oh, my God.

15:46.554 --> 15:48.599
- Yeah, sending three gunmen,

15:48.643 --> 15:51.080
Fedorova clearly has
a big problem with you.

15:52.255 --> 15:53.691
- Val.

15:53.735 --> 15:55.215
- Two of the shooters are DOA.

15:55.258 --> 15:58.174
The third's in custody
and being transported.

15:58.218 --> 16:00.611
- A shoot-out, Val,
with you in the middle?

16:00.655 --> 16:04.441
What is this,
Fedorova upping her game?

16:04.485 --> 16:05.573
- Did you speak to her?

16:05.616 --> 16:07.488
- She denied involvement.

16:07.531 --> 16:11.753
- She wasn't cryptic
or confusing or annoying?

16:11.796 --> 16:13.102
- Just denied it.

16:13.146 --> 16:14.886
I'll pursue it further.

16:18.281 --> 16:20.022
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

16:20.066 --> 16:21.067
[siren wailing]

16:21.110 --> 16:23.939
[cell phone buzzing
and ringing]

16:23.983 --> 16:27.203
- Director Réal, we just
got word about the shoot-out.

16:27.247 --> 16:28.378
The MCU interview room is--

16:28.422 --> 16:30.598
- Good, Doak.
Put Anthony Flowers on.

16:31.991 --> 16:33.079
- Of course.

16:35.995 --> 16:36.996
The director.

16:40.564 --> 16:41.957
- This is Flowers.

16:42.001 --> 16:43.872
- I need you to handle
something for me.

16:43.915 --> 16:46.701
Drive to Peekskill Prison for
a sit-down with Owen Turner.

16:46.744 --> 16:48.094
I'll fill you in
on the way.

16:48.137 --> 16:49.356
Don't tell anyone
where you're going.

16:49.399 --> 16:52.359
Not Doak, especially not Val.

16:52.402 --> 16:54.274
Understood?
- Yes, Director.

16:54.317 --> 16:55.362
- Send your cell.

16:55.405 --> 16:56.711
Call back
when you're driving.

16:58.626 --> 17:01.542
- I have to step out, orders.

17:01.585 --> 17:03.283
- Regarding?

17:03.326 --> 17:04.762
- Can't say.

17:04.806 --> 17:07.722
[tense music]

17:07.765 --> 17:14.903
♪

17:16.165 --> 17:17.123
- [yells]

17:17.166 --> 17:18.646
[glass shatters]

17:20.039 --> 17:26.654
♪

17:28.656 --> 17:29.874
[scanner beeps]

17:29.918 --> 17:32.486
- Welcome, Ms. Ojjeh.

17:32.529 --> 17:33.878
- You.

17:37.839 --> 17:39.362
[scanner beeps]

17:39.406 --> 17:41.538
- Welcome, Mr. McPherson.

17:43.627 --> 17:45.238
- Unless one of you
is a Federal Reserve

17:45.281 --> 17:48.023
board member in disguise,
this is the end of the road.

17:48.067 --> 17:50.069
You need three of us
to enter the vault.

17:57.554 --> 17:59.165
[scanner beeps]

18:01.036 --> 18:03.256
- I'll get you a refill,
Ms. Doherty.

18:05.606 --> 18:07.651
- Welcome, Ms. Doherty.

18:14.049 --> 18:17.139
- One down, two to go.
Let's hit it.

18:22.579 --> 18:25.669
[alarm beeping]

18:25.713 --> 18:27.367
- You see, this is where
I become frustrated.

18:27.410 --> 18:29.673
I was told there was no way
to breach the vault door

18:29.717 --> 18:31.980
without a third
board member's biometrics.

18:33.155 --> 18:35.114
They're through
the first vault door.

18:35.157 --> 18:37.899
- Abdel,
Assistant Director Doak.

18:37.942 --> 18:39.988
- Heard you had a hell
of a morning.

18:40.031 --> 18:42.686
Team's assembled outside,
awaiting your download.

18:42.730 --> 18:44.645
- Let's get this over with.

18:47.474 --> 18:49.128
- We pulled the plans for you.

18:49.171 --> 18:51.391
- This is the third shooter
from Abdel's house.

18:51.434 --> 18:54.611
- In the command center,
if that works for you.

18:54.655 --> 18:55.830
Not even sure I'm in charge.

18:55.873 --> 18:57.353
- You are.
- Really?

18:57.397 --> 18:58.963
I get the sense
if this goes pear-shaped,

18:59.007 --> 19:01.314
I'll be selling knish
in Times Square.

19:01.357 --> 19:02.924
- That's probably true
for both of us.

19:02.967 --> 19:04.578
- You didn't get raked
over the coals

19:04.621 --> 19:06.580
by the president's
chief of staff.

19:06.623 --> 19:08.147
Exactly the opposite.

19:08.190 --> 19:09.757
- [sighs]

19:09.800 --> 19:12.325
- When I upgraded the system,
I had them seal a fire door

19:12.368 --> 19:14.022
from the vault level
to the subway tunnel

19:14.065 --> 19:16.590
on the William Street side.

19:16.633 --> 19:17.721
There is a vulnerable spot.

19:17.765 --> 19:18.940
It's just brick and drywall.

19:18.983 --> 19:21.116
No rebar.
We can break through.

19:21.160 --> 19:23.771
- I'll take a small detail,
go in quiet.

19:23.814 --> 19:25.599
Be in and gone
before they even know it.

19:25.642 --> 19:27.340
- I'll get him
into the server.

19:27.383 --> 19:28.645
You question the prisoner.

19:29.777 --> 19:31.648
- Um, Doak?

19:32.823 --> 19:36.044
Listen,
Abdel is skittish.

19:36.087 --> 19:37.132
- Interviews
are your specialty,

19:37.176 --> 19:39.221
and we need the best
in that room.

19:39.265 --> 19:42.268
- And the president
is watching.

19:42.311 --> 19:43.921
- Yes.

19:43.965 --> 19:45.836
So if it's flawless,

19:45.880 --> 19:49.623
it's commendations for me
and reinstatement for you.

19:49.666 --> 19:50.841
What do you say?

19:51.886 --> 19:53.496
- I'm all about teamwork.

19:53.540 --> 20:00.677
♪

20:04.377 --> 20:05.943
- Your name, please?

20:05.987 --> 20:07.249
- Ameera Ojjeh.

20:07.293 --> 20:09.208
[scanner beeping]
- Recognized.

20:10.513 --> 20:11.862
Your name, please?

20:13.386 --> 20:15.301
- Scott McPherson.

20:15.344 --> 20:16.780
[scanner beeping]

20:16.824 --> 20:18.042
- Recognized.

20:22.699 --> 20:24.875
Your name, please?

20:24.919 --> 20:26.790
[recorder beeps]
- Seamus Plymouth.

20:26.834 --> 20:28.270
You have a delivery for me?
- Depends.

20:28.314 --> 20:30.838
Are you Federal Reserve
board member

20:30.881 --> 20:32.274
"See-moose Ply-mouth"?

20:32.318 --> 20:34.015
- It's pronounced
"Shay-mus Plih-muth."

20:34.058 --> 20:36.931
Want a tip?
Next time, get it right.

20:36.974 --> 20:38.976
- Have a good day.

20:39.020 --> 20:40.543
- Recognized.

20:40.587 --> 20:42.415
- [laughs]

20:50.814 --> 20:52.251
- Two down, one to go.

20:54.078 --> 20:55.689
- The entry point
is very close.

20:55.732 --> 20:57.604
This way.

20:58.431 --> 21:00.520
- Sir, vault two
has been breached.

21:00.563 --> 21:02.391
- Snow White is through
the second vault door.

21:02.435 --> 21:04.785
- Don't worry, they won't
get through the third.

21:04.828 --> 21:07.744
It's iris recognition.
You can't fake that.

21:08.441 --> 21:10.051
Okay, unless they have
a board member's eyeball

21:10.094 --> 21:12.836
in their pocket,
they're not getting through.

21:12.880 --> 21:20.017
♪

21:24.370 --> 21:25.284
- Oh, my God.

21:28.069 --> 21:29.200
[device beeps]

21:30.898 --> 21:33.727
- This is it.
I marked it, just in case.

21:33.770 --> 21:34.989
- Vault sensors
are picking up

21:35.032 --> 21:37.078
a strong heat signature
at the third door.

21:37.121 --> 21:38.688
Tech thinks
it's an explosive device,

21:38.732 --> 21:39.776
and it's just been armed.

21:39.820 --> 21:41.778
We need to get in now!

21:41.822 --> 21:42.997
- Yes, sir.

21:50.352 --> 21:50.526
.

21:50.570 --> 21:52.920
[insects chirping]

21:52.963 --> 21:55.357
[dramatic music]

21:55.401 --> 21:57.707
- He doesn't look well.

21:57.751 --> 21:59.230
- I've been watching him
for days.

21:59.274 --> 22:01.711
He never left the house.

22:01.755 --> 22:03.670
He has a problem with alcohol.

22:05.976 --> 22:08.065
How the mighty have fallen.

22:08.109 --> 22:10.546
- Let's do this tonight.

22:11.460 --> 22:12.766
- [speaking Russian]

22:14.202 --> 22:15.595
- I don't feel well.

22:16.509 --> 22:18.641
- About this?
Him?

22:18.685 --> 22:21.905
- For weeks now,
it comes and goes.

22:21.949 --> 22:23.864
I thought I had the flu.

22:26.040 --> 22:29.348
I think there's
something wrong with me.

22:35.136 --> 22:36.311
What?

22:44.450 --> 22:48.410
- I don't believe this.
[laughs]

22:48.454 --> 22:50.978
- I didn't think
I could have children.

22:51.021 --> 22:52.458
All these years
we've been together--

22:52.501 --> 22:54.068
- It's a miracle.

22:54.111 --> 22:56.984
It's my mother in heaven
sending us a blessing.

22:57.027 --> 23:03.991
♪

23:18.484 --> 23:20.660
- Anthony.

23:22.313 --> 23:23.445
How you doing?

23:23.489 --> 23:24.620
- Owen.

23:24.664 --> 23:26.666
- It's good to see you.

23:26.709 --> 23:28.407
- Yeah, it's not a social call.

23:30.365 --> 23:32.585
Val was involved
in a shoot-out today.

23:32.628 --> 23:34.891
- Oh.
- She's fine.

23:34.935 --> 23:37.981
- Shoot-out?

23:38.025 --> 23:39.592
With who?

23:39.635 --> 23:42.682
- See, that's a question
that I'm inclined to ask you,

23:42.725 --> 23:45.336
but there's not a lot of
honesty coming from your camp.

23:45.380 --> 23:47.861
So I'll just say
what I'm here to say.

23:47.904 --> 23:51.517
- Anthony, I don't know
anything about a shoot-out.

23:51.560 --> 23:53.823
- Maybe that's true, maybe not.

23:53.867 --> 23:56.347
I don't know you anymore,
but whatever you're involved in

23:56.391 --> 23:58.959
put Val
in front of flying lead.

23:59.002 --> 24:02.789
So I'm just here to ask,
was that the original goal?

24:02.832 --> 24:05.226
- I don't know anything
about it.

24:05.269 --> 24:06.662
- I have to assume

24:06.706 --> 24:08.403
that you got involved
with these people

24:08.447 --> 24:11.928
because whatever they sold you
sounded like the right path,

24:11.972 --> 24:14.104
or maybe it was
part of it all along.

24:14.148 --> 24:16.193
- Now, you know I would never
put her in jeopardy.

24:16.237 --> 24:18.544
- But she is,

24:18.587 --> 24:20.023
because the people
you're working with

24:20.067 --> 24:21.721
just tried
to take out your wife.

24:21.764 --> 24:23.766
- No.
That's not it.

24:23.810 --> 24:27.553
- The same woman who stood
by you when no one else would.

24:28.858 --> 24:31.905
Owen, if you knew
it was coming,

24:31.948 --> 24:33.602
just clam up.

24:35.082 --> 24:37.476
But if this is out of hand,
which it is,

24:37.519 --> 24:38.738
get out now.

24:40.391 --> 24:43.438
And I'll do anything
I can to help.

24:47.964 --> 24:50.837
Okay, okay.

24:52.752 --> 24:56.538
Just ask yourself
one question, then.

24:56.582 --> 24:59.062
Is this really who you are now?

24:59.106 --> 25:06.069
♪

25:10.160 --> 25:11.118
- Go.

25:13.294 --> 25:15.383
[scanner beeping]

25:15.426 --> 25:16.689
- Recognized.

25:20.649 --> 25:23.478
[drywall crumbling]

25:29.005 --> 25:30.964
- How long will it take
to reset the system?

25:32.531 --> 25:34.576
- No more than a few minutes.

25:38.145 --> 25:39.799
- Can you open this?

25:39.842 --> 25:41.540
We can send in a team
to take them out.

25:41.583 --> 25:44.238
- Have to retake the system
to open the door.

25:44.281 --> 25:45.674
Then it's all yours.

25:46.545 --> 25:49.460
- Val, tell everyone topside
that we're in the server room.

25:49.504 --> 25:50.853
[static crackling]

25:50.897 --> 25:52.507
Val.

25:57.947 --> 26:02.386
- Ivan Aslanov,
here on a student visa.

26:02.430 --> 26:04.214
[glass shatters]

26:04.258 --> 26:06.565
So what are you studying?

26:06.608 --> 26:07.870
- I have nothing to say.

26:07.914 --> 26:10.481
- Oh, now, now, now.
Not so fast, come on.

26:10.525 --> 26:11.613
One thing you should learn

26:11.657 --> 26:13.093
while getting
your American education

26:13.136 --> 26:16.313
is that this is the land
of let's make a deal.

26:16.357 --> 26:18.707
- Not interested.

26:18.751 --> 26:20.840
- Well, you're in a tough spot.

26:20.883 --> 26:22.450
You had one job to do.

26:22.493 --> 26:24.365
One job.

26:24.408 --> 26:25.627
Take out Ahmed Abdel.

26:25.671 --> 26:26.759
You failed.

26:28.151 --> 26:29.283
What do you think
Elena Fedorova

26:29.326 --> 26:30.806
is gonna do to you
when she finds out?

26:30.850 --> 26:33.200
- What do I care
about Elena Fedorova?

26:33.243 --> 26:34.680
What can she do to me?

26:34.723 --> 26:35.855
- She's your boss.

26:35.898 --> 26:37.639
- I don't work for that bitch.

26:38.814 --> 26:40.816
- You were wearing
Snow White masks.

26:40.860 --> 26:43.036
- Bought at a kiosk
near Grand Central.

26:43.079 --> 26:45.038
His surveillance
would show the masks.

26:46.169 --> 26:47.997
- So his surveillance
shows the masks,

26:48.041 --> 26:50.260
you put it off on Snow White.

26:50.304 --> 26:52.611
Okay, so if you don't work
for Elena Fedorova,

26:52.654 --> 26:54.090
who do you work for?

26:56.745 --> 27:00.009
'Cause we keep hearing
the name Belok.

27:02.621 --> 27:04.666
- I'd like my lawyer.

27:04.710 --> 27:08.278
See, I do know about America.

27:08.322 --> 27:09.845
I watch TV.

27:12.282 --> 27:14.371
[scanner beeping]

27:14.415 --> 27:15.851
- Recognized.

27:17.592 --> 27:19.115
[alarm beeping]

27:19.159 --> 27:22.684
- Second iris has been scanned
outside the gold vault.

27:22.728 --> 27:25.208
- Get Doak on the radio.
Make sure he's aware.

27:25.252 --> 27:27.297
[static crackling]

27:27.341 --> 27:28.690
- Maybe they're out of range.

27:28.734 --> 27:30.736
- They shouldn't be.
Send an agent down.

27:32.085 --> 27:33.652
I can't make sense of it, sir.

27:33.695 --> 27:34.914
I've interviewed
two of her people.

27:34.957 --> 27:36.393
They never denied
being Snow White.

27:36.437 --> 27:37.699
In fact, they revel in it.

27:37.743 --> 27:39.396
So I'm leaning toward
believing his story.

27:39.440 --> 27:40.833
- So who is he?

27:40.876 --> 27:42.573
- No record in the U.S.,
nothing with Interpol.

27:42.617 --> 27:45.881
But he's trained well
and acts like she's an enemy.

27:45.925 --> 27:47.883
When I mentioned the Beloks,
he lawyered up.

27:47.927 --> 27:49.058
- If he's with the Beloks,

27:49.102 --> 27:51.844
why go after
another enemy of hers?

27:51.887 --> 27:54.673
We brought Abdel in
to spoil Elena's plan.

27:55.761 --> 27:58.241
- But I like the idea
of teamwork.

27:58.285 --> 28:00.374
- Teamwork.

28:00.417 --> 28:01.854
- Now, now, you never know

28:01.897 --> 28:03.769
when someone might turn out
to be a true partner.

28:05.466 --> 28:06.946
- Sir, does she look worried?

28:08.730 --> 28:10.340
- Not a bit.

28:10.384 --> 28:12.299
- I got a bad feeling.

28:12.342 --> 28:13.430
- Abdel is in the photo.

28:13.474 --> 28:15.345
He must be her target.

28:15.389 --> 28:16.695
- Unless she turned him...

28:21.221 --> 28:23.179
And we just walked him
right into the Federal Reserve.

28:25.791 --> 28:26.182
.

28:26.226 --> 28:27.793
[dog barking, birds chirping]

28:29.577 --> 28:31.579
- [whistles]
- [gasps]

28:32.928 --> 28:35.409
- Don't move.

28:36.540 --> 28:39.065
- Mr. Abdel, my name
is Elena Fedorova.

28:39.108 --> 28:41.763
This is my husband,
Sergey Vodianov.

28:41.807 --> 28:42.982
- I know who you are.

28:43.025 --> 28:45.462
- Don't be afraid.
We just want to talk.

28:46.637 --> 28:49.510
- You drink so much, Mr. Abdel.

28:49.553 --> 28:51.381
- Something you're trying
to forget?

28:51.425 --> 28:54.080
- Are you--
are you here to kill me?

28:54.123 --> 28:55.255
- You would deserve it.

28:55.298 --> 28:57.779
- I'm so sorry.

28:57.823 --> 28:59.738
I--I didn't know.

28:59.781 --> 29:01.261
- Only a day ago,

29:01.304 --> 29:03.437
it wouldn't have mattered
that you were sorry.

29:03.480 --> 29:07.484
I felt so much rage
for the people who hurt us.

29:09.965 --> 29:11.967
I've killed people.

29:12.011 --> 29:14.230
I would have killed you.

29:14.274 --> 29:16.885
But I don't want
to do that anymore.

29:16.929 --> 29:18.191
Doesn't change anything.

29:18.234 --> 29:21.803
- No, it doesn't.
- Sit down, don't move.

29:21.847 --> 29:26.199
[sighs]
I need to make the world better

29:26.242 --> 29:29.376
for those who come next.

29:29.419 --> 29:31.334
Perhaps you'd like to help us.

29:31.378 --> 29:34.250
[tense music]

29:34.294 --> 29:37.427
♪

29:37.471 --> 29:40.866
- Time frame, Abdel?
- 20 seconds.

29:47.829 --> 29:49.613
[scanner beeping]

29:49.657 --> 29:51.311
You can do anything
on your phone.

29:51.354 --> 29:54.618
[scanner beeping]

30:00.363 --> 30:02.191
- What are you doing
with propane?

30:03.192 --> 30:04.411
[scanner beeps]

30:08.545 --> 30:11.026
- Doak, get Abdel
out of there.

30:11.070 --> 30:12.158
He's with Snow White.

30:12.201 --> 30:13.899
I'm on my way.

30:13.942 --> 30:16.423
- Freeze!
Don't move!

30:16.466 --> 30:19.208
- It's--it's too late.
It's done.

30:21.384 --> 30:25.736
[door clanks and whirs]

30:25.780 --> 30:32.656
♪

30:32.700 --> 30:34.136
- Take them back up
to the lobby.

30:34.180 --> 30:35.572
I'll handle this.

30:37.444 --> 30:39.794
- Do not set off that device!

30:39.838 --> 30:46.627
♪

30:56.332 --> 30:58.117
- We need to unlock
this door right now.

30:58.160 --> 30:59.727
- No, we need to leave.

30:59.770 --> 31:02.208
They're planting propane tanks
in the vault.

31:02.251 --> 31:03.644
The device will set them off

31:03.687 --> 31:06.255
and the room will become
an oven, over 2,000 degrees.

31:06.299 --> 31:08.127
- The gold will vaporize.

31:08.170 --> 31:09.171
- Why?
What does that prove?

31:09.215 --> 31:10.477
- It's Gambia.

31:10.520 --> 31:12.174
It's the diamond mine
she imploded.

31:12.218 --> 31:13.436
It's not about the money.

31:13.480 --> 31:14.873
It's about revenge.

31:14.916 --> 31:16.178
- Get a demo team
and the bomb squad

31:16.222 --> 31:17.223
to blow this door.

31:17.266 --> 31:18.354
- You don't have time for that.

31:18.398 --> 31:20.443
- We have charges.
- Take it now!

31:20.487 --> 31:26.928
♪

31:31.150 --> 31:32.499
[explosion]

31:41.464 --> 31:43.684
[timer beeping]

31:43.727 --> 31:44.685
- Freeze!

31:50.256 --> 31:51.648
- You all better run.

31:51.692 --> 31:53.955
- We got a lobby
full of hostages upstairs

31:53.999 --> 31:54.913
and no time to evacuate.

31:56.392 --> 31:57.959
Just under a minute.

31:58.003 --> 31:59.830
- Take the prisoners back out
through the tunnel.

31:59.874 --> 32:01.963
- Due respect, sir, we should
stay till the room is clear.

32:02.007 --> 32:03.312
- That's an order!

32:03.356 --> 32:05.053
- Let's go, everybody out.

32:06.968 --> 32:09.231
- You remember ordnance class
at Quantico?

32:09.275 --> 32:10.580
- Some of it.

32:10.624 --> 32:11.886
We could try cutting the wires,

32:11.930 --> 32:13.844
but if it has
collapsing circuits,

32:13.888 --> 32:15.455
then it detonates.

32:15.498 --> 32:17.152
- We could try to relocate it
to a safe place,

32:17.196 --> 32:19.328
but if it has a mercury switch
that's sensitive to movement...

32:19.372 --> 32:22.331
- It detonates, and there's
no safe place to relocate it.

32:22.375 --> 32:25.552
- Last option:
remove the detonators.

32:25.595 --> 32:27.641
If there's
no trigger mechanism,

32:27.684 --> 32:29.730
the primary explosive
is neutralized.

32:33.299 --> 32:35.083
- I'll take one.
You take the other.

32:36.302 --> 32:37.477
Real easy, Val.

32:37.520 --> 32:40.567
- Three, two, one, pull.

32:40.610 --> 32:43.526
[suspenseful music]

32:43.570 --> 32:45.050
♪

32:45.093 --> 32:46.138
- Take cover.

32:46.181 --> 32:47.661
- There's no point.

32:47.704 --> 32:49.402
Either it worked, or it didn't.
Cross your fingers.

32:49.445 --> 32:52.448
[timer beeping]

32:53.362 --> 32:54.494
[device clicks]

33:01.936 --> 33:03.068
Teamwork.

33:04.156 --> 33:05.548
- Let's finish this.

33:06.767 --> 33:09.291
Stand by for the go order.

33:09.335 --> 33:11.032
We're retaking
the Federal Reserve.

33:11.076 --> 33:14.035
[dramatic music]

33:14.079 --> 33:17.169
♪

33:17.212 --> 33:18.300
Take the door.

33:18.344 --> 33:20.607
- Moving in.

33:20.650 --> 33:22.217
- On the ground now!

33:22.261 --> 33:23.436
- FBI!
Show me your hands!

33:23.479 --> 33:25.525
- Down, down now!

33:29.616 --> 33:30.008
.

33:30.051 --> 33:32.532
[tense music]

33:32.575 --> 33:39.539
♪

33:41.932 --> 33:44.196
[machine clunks]

33:44.239 --> 33:46.720
- When they came for Abdel,

33:46.763 --> 33:48.504
they fired on Val.

33:48.548 --> 33:50.376
They must have been wearing
Snow White masks.

33:52.117 --> 33:53.901
- A message for us.

33:55.120 --> 33:56.338
- They could have killed her.

33:56.382 --> 33:58.210
- Beloks are no match
for your wife.

33:58.253 --> 34:00.255
- That's not the point.

34:01.865 --> 34:04.781
You said the plan
could draw them out,

34:04.825 --> 34:06.044
but you never told me

34:06.087 --> 34:09.090
that Val could get caught
in the crossfire.

34:09.134 --> 34:11.484
- Did you think
it was gonna be easy?

34:11.527 --> 34:15.096
Elena is doing everything
she can to protect her.

34:15.140 --> 34:18.099
- You better hope
that's enough,

34:18.143 --> 34:20.623
because if anything
happens to Val...

34:22.669 --> 34:24.410
I'll kill you both.

34:26.151 --> 34:27.717
Remember that.

34:27.761 --> 34:34.681
♪

34:35.812 --> 34:37.292
[machine clunks]

34:38.728 --> 34:40.904
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

34:40.948 --> 34:42.732
[siren wailing]

34:42.776 --> 34:45.387
- I should probably thank you
for saving my life earlier.

34:47.128 --> 34:48.521
- Don't mention it.

34:48.564 --> 34:51.741
Abdel, before you're locked up,
help me understand.

34:51.785 --> 34:55.745
The shooters who came for you,
no records here or abroad.

34:55.789 --> 34:57.704
They're ghosts.

34:57.747 --> 35:00.141
But if I had to guess,

35:00.185 --> 35:03.101
I'd say they were hired
by the Beloks.

35:03.927 --> 35:05.277
- That's a good guess.

35:05.320 --> 35:08.149
- Not a lot of information
available.

35:08.193 --> 35:09.455
They're a crime family?

35:09.498 --> 35:11.152
- Mm-hmm.

35:11.196 --> 35:14.460
- Enemies of Elena Fedorova,
Snow White?

35:14.503 --> 35:15.504
- Long time.

35:16.505 --> 35:18.333
That's probably
all I should say.

35:19.682 --> 35:21.119
- How'd she turned you?

35:22.816 --> 35:25.166
You seem like a--a smart,

35:25.210 --> 35:26.994
freethinking person.

35:27.037 --> 35:28.126
- Like your husband?

35:30.040 --> 35:31.477
- We're discussing you.

35:31.520 --> 35:34.697
- The tactics were probably
different for me and Owen,

35:34.741 --> 35:37.178
different but the same.

35:37.222 --> 35:40.007
- Put a word to it.

35:40.050 --> 35:43.271
- Willingness.
I lied before.

35:43.315 --> 35:44.577
I wasn't pulled into the room

35:44.620 --> 35:46.883
just to guide
the surveillance drone.

35:46.927 --> 35:51.192
I--I arranged payment
to the bomber, Pasha Antonov.

35:51.236 --> 35:53.629
You could say I hired him,
technically.

35:53.673 --> 35:55.675
- Did you know
what you were paying him to do?

35:55.718 --> 35:57.111
- No.

35:57.155 --> 35:58.460
I was told it was to help
our allies in Belarus,

35:58.504 --> 36:00.549
working to fight against
Russian aggression.

36:00.593 --> 36:02.072
They lied to me.

36:03.204 --> 36:06.338
I drank to cope.
I--I withdrew.

36:08.601 --> 36:13.258
And then Elena and Sergey
knocked on my door.

36:14.563 --> 36:16.391
I'm done now.

36:16.435 --> 36:21.614
- Ahmed, I'm all
for redemption,

36:21.657 --> 36:24.573
but prison
is a dangerous place.

36:24.617 --> 36:27.576
If the Beloks want you dead,
they can find you there too.

36:27.620 --> 36:29.230
- Elena won't let
anything happen to me.

36:29.274 --> 36:31.841
- Elena wasn't there
this morning.

36:31.885 --> 36:33.408
I was.

36:33.452 --> 36:35.236
- Yes,

36:35.280 --> 36:37.282
because Elena sent you.

36:39.719 --> 36:42.591
[cell phone ringing]

36:46.856 --> 36:48.423
- Director.

36:48.467 --> 36:50.599
- The messages Elena's
receiving from outside...

36:51.513 --> 36:53.167
Forensics cracked the code.

36:53.211 --> 36:55.343
- And? What'd you learn?

36:55.387 --> 36:57.780
- First, some of the messages

36:57.824 --> 37:00.392
are coming
from inside Peekskill Prison.

37:01.654 --> 37:03.133
- Owen.

37:03.177 --> 37:04.787
- I sent Flowers to visit him
and to let him know

37:04.831 --> 37:08.008
about the attack
at Ahmed Abdel's house

37:08.051 --> 37:10.402
just to see
if he'd reach out to Elena.

37:10.445 --> 37:15.058
The latest message reads,
"Val and Abdel under fire.

37:15.102 --> 37:16.799
The new players are here."

37:17.452 --> 37:19.324
- He knows about the Beloks.

37:19.367 --> 37:20.542
- It's a lot to process.

37:20.586 --> 37:22.892
But I don't want you
visiting him again,

37:22.936 --> 37:24.590
not without a wire.

37:24.633 --> 37:26.156
It's too risky.

37:29.377 --> 37:31.118
- I was ordered, Val.

37:31.161 --> 37:32.554
- Do not apologize, Anthony.

37:32.598 --> 37:34.252
- It wasn't something
I felt good about.

37:34.295 --> 37:36.732
But at the same time,
I gotta say...

37:36.776 --> 37:39.126
I didn't hate
giving him a piece of my mind.

37:40.562 --> 37:42.172
- Look, um,

37:42.216 --> 37:43.783
did he seem upset

37:43.826 --> 37:46.394
when you told him about
what happened at Abdel's house?

37:46.438 --> 37:48.614
- Yeah, he was upset.

37:48.657 --> 37:52.574
- It's just the message
he sent Elena was so, um...

37:52.618 --> 37:54.663
straightforward.

37:54.707 --> 37:58.276
I'm just--I'm trying
to make it make sense

37:58.319 --> 38:00.234
in--in--in my head.

38:01.627 --> 38:03.716
[sighs]

38:03.759 --> 38:06.806
Maybe I'm trying to make it
something it's not.

38:06.849 --> 38:08.242
- Don't know, Val.

38:10.636 --> 38:13.900
- It all comes out to the same.

38:16.163 --> 38:19.514
Owen made his choice.

38:22.343 --> 38:24.954
He's with Elena,

38:24.998 --> 38:26.434
not me.

38:28.828 --> 38:31.309
- Chief of Staff Swanstrom
wants us to conference.

38:32.701 --> 38:34.399
Victory lap, Val.

38:37.445 --> 38:39.795
- Take it.
You earned it.

38:39.839 --> 38:42.320
- I'm not in the mood.

38:42.363 --> 38:45.323
[somber music]

38:45.366 --> 38:48.456
♪

38:48.500 --> 38:50.806
- Great news all around.

38:50.850 --> 38:52.721
The president was thrilled
to hear it.

38:52.765 --> 38:55.245
- Well...

38:55.289 --> 38:56.682
the job had to get done.

38:57.900 --> 38:59.380
I got it done.

38:59.424 --> 39:02.383
[suspenseful music]

39:02.427 --> 39:09.521
♪

39:14.395 --> 39:15.701
[device beeping]

39:28.322 --> 39:29.279
- Freeze!

39:29.323 --> 39:36.417
♪

39:40.465 --> 39:41.683
[buzzer blares]

39:48.124 --> 39:50.475
- I'll never understand it.

39:50.518 --> 39:52.564
There's, like, a piece missing.

39:52.607 --> 39:55.436
What's the one thing
that turns a person

39:55.480 --> 40:00.441
from normal human being
to zealot?

40:00.485 --> 40:03.139
- Willingness?

40:03.183 --> 40:05.054
For us, it was our baby.

40:05.098 --> 40:08.362
We wanted a better life,
a better world for our child.

40:08.406 --> 40:09.711
- As most mothers do.

40:09.755 --> 40:11.539
- Giving birth does not
make you soft,

40:11.583 --> 40:13.280
quite the opposite.

40:14.586 --> 40:16.849
You know what's easy?

40:16.892 --> 40:19.460
Murder, violence.

40:19.504 --> 40:23.203
What is hard is forgiveness.

40:23.246 --> 40:24.726
If you had the chance,

40:24.770 --> 40:27.250
would you forgive Isaac Bigby
for killing your mother?

40:27.294 --> 40:28.730
- This again.

40:28.774 --> 40:33.822
- If you had the opportunity
to right that wrong

40:33.866 --> 40:35.737
and if there was someone
who understood--

40:35.781 --> 40:39.872
- Is that what turned someone
like Abdel to Snow White?

40:41.526 --> 40:42.875
Well, it doesn't apply to me.

40:42.918 --> 40:44.485
- Hmm, let's see.

40:44.529 --> 40:46.487
Check your pocket.

40:46.531 --> 40:53.320
♪

40:55.931 --> 40:59.108
Isaac Bigby's address.

40:59.152 --> 41:01.023
He's alive.

41:02.068 --> 41:04.418
For all these years,

41:04.462 --> 41:06.855
there's been no accountability,

41:06.899 --> 41:09.336
no justice.

41:12.600 --> 41:15.342
So now it's time for you

41:15.385 --> 41:17.083
to tell me a story.

41:19.564 --> 41:22.480
And I'm dying to know
how it ends.
